Additional Information: SARS Virus Indirect Immunofluorescence Test
--------------------------------------------------
[This information supplements that received previously from Dr.
Niedrig (Robert Koch Institute, Berlin, Germany) - see: SARS -
worldwide (133): diagnostic testing 20030604.1373. - Mod.CP]
In collaboration with the Robert Koch Institute, Berlin, Germany, the
company EUROIMMUN of Luebeck, Germany, has manufactured slides with 2
biochips, one of them coated with SARS-coronavirus
(SARS-CoV)-infected cells, the other with non-infected cells. The
slides can be used as an indirect immunofluorescence test (IIFT). A
large number of SARS patients have already been analyzed by IIFT
using these slides. Positive reactions were observed in almost all
sera from more than 150 SARS patients, while more than 500 sera from
healthy blood donors, contact persons, or patients with other virus
infections, e.g. HIV, HCV, or HBV, were all negative. The slides can
now be ordered from EUROIMMUN. Further information can be found on
our website:

--
Dr. Christof Lehmann, Ph.D.
EUROIMMUN AG
